# Kubernetes Manifests Standards  
- One resource per file, or logically grouped (Deployment + Service)
- Filename: `<kind>-<name>.yaml` lowercase (deployment-api.yaml, service-api.yaml)
- Use `---` separator for multiple resources in single file
- Create new chart based on the best practice for example kube-prometheus-stack chart

Every resource must have:
```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: myapp
  namespace: production      # always explicit, never rely on context
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: myapp
    app.kubernetes.io/component: api
    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: platform
```

## Labels Convention
Follow kubernetes recommended labels:
- `app.kubernetes.io/name` - application name
- `app.kubernetes.io/instance` - instance identifier
- `app.kubernetes.io/version` - app version
- `app.kubernetes.io/component` - component within architecture
- `app.kubernetes.io/part-of` - higher level application
- `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by` - tool managing resource

## ConfigMaps and Secrets
- Use `stringData` for Secrets (base64 auto-encoded)
- Add checksum annotation for pod restart on config change
- Never commit real secrets, use placeholders or sealed-secrets

## Do NOT
- Use `latest` tag for images
- Omit namespace in manifests
- Set cpu limits without understanding throttling implications
- Use hostPath volumes in production
- Run containers as root without explicit reason

# Kubernetes Helm charts Standards  
## values.yaml
- Document every value with comments
- Group related values
- Use camelCase for keys
- Provide sensible defaults
```yaml
## Whitespace Control
```yaml
# Remove whitespace before
{{- if .Values.enabled }}
# Remove whitespace after
{{ .Values.name -}}
# Remove both
{{- .Values.name -}}
```

### Indentation
Use `nindent` for proper YAML indentation:
```yaml
metadata:
  labels:
    {{- include "mychart.labels" . | nindent 4 }}
spec:
  template:
    metadata:
      annotations:
        {{- with .Values.podAnnotations }}
        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}
        {{- end }}
```

### Conditionals
```yaml
{{- if .Values.ingress.enabled }}
# resource here
{{- end }}

{{- if and .Values.metrics.enabled .Values.metrics.serviceMonitor.enabled }}
# nested condition
{{- end }}

# Default values
{{ .Values.name | default "myapp" }}
{{ .Values.port | default 8080 | int }}
```

### Loops
```yaml
{{- range .Values.extraEnvVars }}
- name: {{ .name }}
  value: {{ .value | quote }}
{{- end }}

{{- range $key, $value := .Values.configMap }}
{{ $key }}: {{ $value | quote }}
{{- end }}
```

### Required Values
```yaml
{{ required "image.repository is required" .Values.image.repository }}
```

## _helpers.tpl Patterns
```yaml
{{/*
Chart name truncated to 63 chars
*/}}
{{- define "mychart.name" -}}
{{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}

{{/*
Fullname with release
*/}}
{{- define "mychart.fullname" -}}
{{- if .Values.fullnameOverride }}
{{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- else }}
{{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride }}
{{- if contains $name .Release.Name }}
{{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- else }}
{{- printf "%s-%s" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}
{{- end }}
{{- end }}

{{/*
Common labels
*/}}
{{- define "mychart.labels" -}}
helm.sh/chart: {{ include "mychart.chart" . }}
{{ include "mychart.selectorLabels" . }}
app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}
app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}
{{- end }}

{{/*
Selector labels
*/}}
{{- define "mychart.selectorLabels" -}}
app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include "mychart.name" . }}
app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}
{{- end }}
## Quoting Rules
```yaml
# Always quote strings that might be interpreted as numbers/bools
value: {{ .Values.name | quote }}

# For integers, no quotes but cast explicitly
port: {{ .Values.port | int }}

# For environment variables, always quote
- name: MY_VAR
  value: {{ .Values.myVar | quote }}
```

## Debug Templates
```yaml
# Render template output for debugging
helm template mychart . --debug

# Show computed values
helm get values release-name
```

## Do NOT
- Hardcode values that should be configurable
- Use `toYaml` without `nindent`
- Forget whitespace control causing empty lines
- Create circular dependencies in helpers
- Use `required` for values with sensible defaults
